{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#6811: Suspended component still trigger watchers while being switched out",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:36.836777+00:00",
  "text": "Suspended component still trigger watchers while being switched out\n\n### Vue version\n\nlatest\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://sfc.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- click the button\n\n### What is expected?\n\nonly one watcher should trigger\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nboth, the watcher of the leaving and entering component are benig triggered\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nIn this scenario the update of the variable being watched is what triggers the switch\r\n\r\n- https://github.com/vuejs/router/issues/1565\r\n\r\nIs this just a race condition? Since the old component still needs to display, I would say it's normal for it to render due to watchers. This would require vue router to have a special handling of the current route so",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":lady_beetle:  bug",
    "need guidance",
    "scope: suspense"
  ],
